        <Parent_String>etching (printing process) [300053241], intaglio printing processes [300199636], printing processes [300199635], printing and printing processes and techniques [300185289], image-making processes and techniques [300053159], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A printing process in which tone is added to a major part of the print by sprinkling granulated salt on the ground while it is still hot and liquid. Once the plate is cold and the salt has been rinsed away, a random pattern of pits of varied depth is left behind and will create corresponding clusters of black dots on the resulting print.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000016051/Gascoigne, How to Identify Prints (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para el proceso de impresión en el cual la tierra se mezcla con una sustancia suave, tal como sebo, permitiendo la representación de líneas y de áreas texturadas cuando se graba al agua fuerte la placa.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een drukprocedé waarbij kleurstof aan een groot deel van de afdruk wordt toegevoegd door zoutkristallen op de etsgrond te strooien terwijl deze nog heet en vloeibaar is. Wanneer de plaat is afgekoeld en het zout wordt weggespoeld, blijft een willekeurig putjespatroon van uiteenlopende diepte achter, wat overeenkomstige groepen zwarte puntjes op de betreffende afdruk oplevert.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種用以在印刷品增添大片色調的印刷技法。將細鹽撒於炙熱液態的防腐蝕層上，待印版冷卻，鹽份被沖洗掉之後，即留下深度不一的凹點所形成的隨機圖案，在最終的印刷成品上則會製造出相對應的黑點群。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
